    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of two objects, represented by circles, labeled 1 and 2. Object 1 is on the left side and has mass M sub 1. Object 2 is on the right side, has mass M sub 2, and is larger than object 1. A point labeled P is positioned between the two objects, equidistant from the center of each.\" src=\"/images/24c98ccf3d5ddc0811bd25ef1dd91f26.png\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Objects <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> have masses <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 1\"><math alttext=\"M sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, respectively, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"M sub 1 is less than M sub 2\"><math alttext=\"M sub 1 is less than M sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The objects are in outer space far away from any other objects, as shown above. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is located halfway between their centers. At what location, if any, is the gravitational field due to the two objects equal to zero?</p>\n",
